    "UNER dataset [44] is developed by collecting data from news articles from the BBC Urdu website.",
    "It is tagged for seven NE types namely, person, organization, location, designation, time, number, and date, and is a well-structured dataset for Urdu NER tasks, requiring minimum preprocessing effort.",
    "Different statistics of these datasets are shown in Table 2.",
    "Some preprocessing was required before we could use the datasets for experimentation including the addition and removal of spaces between tokens for the improved structure of the multi-word NEs, removal of punctuation marks, filtering duplicate words, handling entangled words with labels, and handling of single letters.",
    "The count of NEs is sufficient in the datasets but in some datasets, the data was not equally distributed causing class imbalance over different NE types."
